en_830542_0	A total of 13 Officers and 143 Other Ranks who followed the Special Infantry Operation Course (SIO) No 64 passed out in a colourful ceremony, held at the Amy Training School in Maduruoya on Tuesday (7).
en_830542_1	Major General Suraj Bansajaya, Commandant, Infantry Training Centre (ITC) graced the occasion as the Chief Guest and he was welcomed by the Commanding Officer, Lieutenant Colonel A.T.S Hennadige.
en_830542_2	A Guard Turnout greeted the Chief Guest on arrival.
en_830542_3	Awards for the Best All Round Officer went to Lieutenant L.L.K.M Alwis of 19 Sri Lanka Vijayabahu Infantry Regiment and the Best All Round Soldier was Corporal A.B.I Wijesena of 19 Gemunu Watch.
